  <summary>7/1/1999--Introduced.
Caregivers Assistance Act of 1999 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to establish a limited tax credit in the case of a taxpayer who is an eligible caregiver equal to $1,000 times the number of individuals needing long-term care (generally, specified individuals with long-term care needs with respect to whom the caregiver is allowed a deduction) who are being cared for by the taxpayer.</summary>
